news.headline: Coffee prices have surged over 100%, hitting record highs since 1977. Prices at $3.90/lb, may soon lead to inflation.
news.summary: Coffee prices in the U.S. have surged to record levels last seen in 1977, with a 100% increase in the past year. This surge is due to coffee becoming the best-performing asset of 2025, rising 20% in just over a month. Arabica coffee futures have climbed for 10 consecutive sessions, with prices reaching $3.90 per pound. This increase could lead to higher coffee retail prices, potentially causing inflation for consumers. With demand high and supply chains strained, a $10 cup of coffee may be on the horizon. Companies in the coffee supply chain may benefit from this price surge.

news.headline: Disney Q1 Earnings: Revenue expected to reach $24.6B, EPS at $1.45. Analysts predict beats fueled by 'Moana 2,' 'Mufasa'. Strengthened segments may lead to continued streak.

The company has surpassed revenue estimates in the last two quarters and in five out of the last 10 quarters. Analysts also predict earnings per share to rise to $1.45 from $1.22, with Disney having beaten EPS estimates in the last six quarters and in eight of the last 10 quarters. Goldman Sachs analyst Michael Ng highlights the importance of Disney's sports, direct-to-consumer, and theme park segments in driving revenue growth. Ng has a Buy rating on the stock and raised the price target to $139 in January, suggesting that Disney could surpass EPS estimates due to the performance of its various business units.
